             <div id="summary-source-credit">Source: Wikipedia</div>
          
          <div id="summary">
            <p>The <b>Firearm Owners' Protection Act</b> of 1986 (<b>FOPA</b>) is a United States federal law that revised many provisions of the Gun Control Act of 1968.
</p>

<p>This summary is from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Firearm_Owners_Protection_Act">Wikipedia</a>.</p>
