				<!-- What is a bill? -->
				<span class="fas fa-circle-info" aria-hidden="true" style="float: right; font-size: 150%; color: white; margin: -2px"></span>
				<h3 style="margin: 0 0 5px 0; font-weight: bold;">S. 49 (99th) was a bill in the United States Congress.</h3>
				<p>A bill must be passed by both the House and Senate in identical form and then be signed by the President to become law.</p>
				<p>Bills numbers restart every two years. That means there are other bills with the number S. 49. This is the one from the 99<sup>th</sup> Congress.</p>
				<p>This bill was introduced in the 99<sup>th</sup> Congress, which met from Jan 3, 1985 to Oct 18, 1986. Legislation not passed by the end of a Congress is cleared from the books.</p>

				<!-- Citation -->
				<h3 style="margin: 0 0 5px 0; font-weight: bold;">
